claim.claim-text:
1. A method of determining the center of focus in a lithography device utilizing latent image analysis, comprising the steps of 
providing a substrate comprising a plurality of latent image diffraction gratings made utilizing the lithography device, the plurality of diffraction gratings comprising different known focus settings; 
determining a diffraction signature for at least three of the plurality of latent image diffraction gratings by means of a radiation source-based tool; 
measuring the differences between the diffraction signatures between adjacent focus setting latent image diffraction gratings; and 
determining the center of focus as the focus setting wherein there is a minimal difference between the diffraction signatures of adjacent focus setting latent image diffraction gratings.

23. A method of determining the center of focus in a lithography device utilizing exposed wafers prior to development of the exposed wafers, comprising the steps of 
providing a wafer comprising a plurality of latent image diffraction gratings made utilizing the lithography device, the plurality of diffraction gratings comprising different known focus settings, wherein the wafer has not been subjected to a development process; 
determining a diffraction signature for at least three of the plurality of latent image diffraction gratings by means of a radiation source-based tool; 
measuring the differences between the diffraction signatures between adjacent focus setting latent image diffraction gratings; and 
determining the center of focus as the focus setting wherein there is a minimal difference between the diffraction signatures of adjacent focus setting latent image diffraction gratings.

45. A method of process control for center of focus in a lithography device, comprising the steps of 
providing a substrate comprising a plurality of diffraction gratings made utilizing the lithography device, the plurality of diffraction gratings comprising different known focus settings; 
determining a diffraction signature for at least three of the plurality of latent image diffraction gratings by means of a radiation source-based tool; 
measuring the differences between the diffraction signatures between adjacent focus setting latent image diffraction gratings; 
determining the center of focus as the focus setting wherein there is a minimal difference between the diffraction signatures of adjacent focus setting latent image diffraction gratings; and 
adjusting the focus setting of the lithography device to the determined center of focus.
